Ve n te r (
Fig. 12
). Peritrematal shields truncated at level of fourth pair of coxae, between level of S 1 -R 1 , separated by triangular slit from podonotal shield, and ornamented by longitudinal fissures. Peritremes extremely short. Both peritrematal setae very finely pilose, r 3 six times as long as r 1 . Sternal shield 46–50 μm long, 37–40 μm wide at level of setae st 2 , posterior margin slightly concave. Adgenital platelets small, bearing 2 gland-openings of gv 2 . One pair of post-genital sclerites often present. Ventri-anal shield with 7 pairs of preanal setae, posteriorly fused to opisthonotal shield. All ventral setae smooth or finely pilose. Ventri-anal pores situated near adanal setae, in posterolateral direction. Anal valves with vestigial euanal setae. Sternal shield with reticulate ornamentation, ventri-anal shield covered by tile-like pattern.

Male (
Figs 13–14
). Length of idiosoma: 210–215 μm; width 151–154 μm (n= 2 ).
